  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "mutt security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mutt is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Mutt is a small but very powerful text-based mail client for Unix operating systems.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nmutt before version 2.3.2 sometimes uses strfcpy instead of memcpy for the IMAP auth_cram MD5 digest, which may lead to buffer handling issues.(CVE-2026-43859)\n\nMutt email client before version 2.3.2 contains a vulnerability where the hash_passwd is sometimes truncated by one byte during IMAP auth_cram MD5 digest authentication, potentially causing authentication failures or security issues.(CVE-2026-43860)\n\nmutt before 2.3.2 does not check for '\\0' in url_pct_decode, resulting in improper null byte handling vulnerability.(CVE-2026-43861)\n\nIn mutt before version 2.3.2, the imap_auth_gss security level is mishandled, which may lead to security vulnerabilities.(CVE-2026-43862)\n\nmutt before 2.3.2 has an infinite loop in data_object_to_stream in crypt-gpgme.c.(CVE-2026-43863)\n\nmutt before version 2.3.2 has a NULL pointer dereference vulnerability in the show_sig_summary function.(CVE-2026-43864)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mutt is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "mutt",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
